        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 5:08AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 508 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 5 miles
northwest of Pat Mayse Lake, moving north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Ord...                            Grant...
Corinne...                        Kent...
Soper...                          Rattan...
Fallon...                         Sobol...
Goodland...                       Sawyer...
Messer...                         Hugo Lake State Park...
Apple...                          Speer...
Dela...                           Hugo...
Kellond...                        Oleta...
Antlers...                        Gay...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 AM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
